-- Deutsche Bahn Initial Public Offering Not on Agenda, Ramsauer Tells Focus
-- Oliver Suess
-- 2010-07-17T08:12:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/deutsche-bahn-initial-public-offering-not-on-agenda-ramsauer-tells-focus.html

          
          
             An initial public offering for
 Deutsche Bahn AG , Germany’s state rail company, is “currently
not on the agenda,” Transport Minister  Peter Ramsauer  told
Focus magazine in an interview.  
 Improving quality, security, cleanliness, timeliness and
reliability will be the first priorities, the magazine cited
Ramsauer as saying.  
